  "excerpt": "Day 7 simulation: using Iran's blackout duration as the clock, we estimate how much GDP would be lost per day if each major economy's own internet were down.",
  "body_paragraphs": [
    "This post does not say these economies are currently losing money because Iran is offline. It uses Iran's blackout duration as a time clock and simulates what a same-length domestic internet blackout would cost each economy on day 7.",
    "Under the world scenario, a blackout of this length implies $35.28B in daily GDP loss and $221.05B in cumulative loss since day 1.",
    "For the large-economy scenarios, the biggest simulated daily losses today are: United States: $10.31B/day; China: $5.54B/day; Germany: $1.50B/day.",
    "Method: 2025 nominal GDP baseline × country-specific digital sensitivity coefficient × an outage-duration escalation curve that gets harsher as the blackout continues."
